      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection and hemolysis constitutive model justified by literature evidence and sensitivity to model form alternatives documented.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on demonstrated superiority for rotating machinery flows with adverse pressure gradients (Menter 1994; literature survey of 12 blood pump CFD studies). Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model selected as regulatory standard. Alternative turbulence models (RNG k-epsilon, RSM) evaluated in the UQ campaign appendix; NIH predictions vary by <12% across model alternatives, within experimental uncertainty. Model form requirement met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
