      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key input parameters (viscosity, density, inlet velocity profile, rotational speed) characterized with uncertainty bounds; dominant inputs identified.",
      "rationale": "Input parameter uncertainty characterization performed as part of the UQ campaign. Blood analog density (1050 ± 5 kg/m³), dynamic viscosity (3.5 ± 0.3 mPa·s), inlet velocity profile (fully developed turbulent, Re uncertainty ±3%), rotational speed (±10 RPM). Sobol first-order indices from the UQ campaign identify rotational speed and flow rate as dominant inputs (combined 87% of variance). Model inputs factor requirement met at MRL 2."
    },
