    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 (CPB hemolysis prediction, MRL 2) is accepted. All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The 6 not-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 with documented justification. Experimental validation against the FDA generic centrifugal pump benchmark demonstrates MAE of 8.4% with all predictions within experimental uncertainty. The UQ campaign (n=128 LHS samples, Sobol indices computed) documented in UQR-CPB-2024-002 confirms model robustness across the operating envelope with 100% of samples satisfying RH < 1. The CFD model is judged sufficiently credible to support the regulatory decision of identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
